<br>
Personally I think it is a turn for the better. Items will no longer be the focus. I think a lot of gamers are getting burnt out by item acquisition now as well, there is only so many items that one can think of, only so many stats that one can attain before there is no further to go, no challenge. <br>
<br>
Welcome to the new challenge: Character Character Development (My own phrase). You don't develop your character's stats or gear, you develop their character! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
But to the topic at hand: I did hear at one point that there would be no transferring of anything between the two games, but that was a while ago and they may have changed their minds. Personally I can see that they would allow it, IF the work involved wasn't so huge (how many items will they have to keep track of being brought across, and can they make it auto-matic or will the two games be totally different file systems).<br>
